Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven to 425 degrees. Bring @butter{2%tbsp} to room temperature. Wash and dry all produce. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Pick @Tarragon{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; discard stems. Mince leaves until you have 1 TBSP. Quarter and core @Apple{1}. Grate 1 quarter on the largest holes of a #box grater; thinly slice remaining apple.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{5%tsp}, half the @Herbes de Provence{1%tsp}, and a generous pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until golden brown and tender, ~{25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #large bowl{}, whisk together @olive oil{1%tbsp}, half the @Red Wine Vinegar{5%tsp}, half the @Dijon Mustard{1%tsp}, ½ tsp minced tarragon, @Sugar{1/2%tsp}, salt, and pepper.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{4%tbsp}, remaining mustard, and 1 1/2 tsp minced tarragon. Season with salt and pepper.

In a second large bowl, combine @Ground Beef{10%ounce}, grated apple, remaining minced tarragon, remaining @Herbes de Provence{1%tsp}, and salt, and pepper. Form into two equal-sized patties, each slightly wider than a burger bun. Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add patties; cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. In the last ~{2%minutes} of cooking, top patties with @Gruyère Cheese{1/2%cup}; cover pan to melt.

Halve @Brioche Buns{2} and spread with softened @butter{2%tbsp}; toast until golden brown. To bowl with vinaigrette, add @Arugula{2%ounce} (reserving a handful for topping burgers), sliced apple, @Almonds{1%ounce}, salt, and pepper; toss to coat. Spread half the aioli onto toasted buns. Fill with patties and reserved arugula. Serve with potato wedges, salad, and remaining aioli on the side.